                    <h1 class="article-title">Why Train Your Dog?</h1>
                    <ol class="tips-list">
                        <li>Dog training has a number of benefits for both you and your pup that you may not even be aware of.</li>
                        <li>Besides making your dog more well-behaved and a politer pup, dog training can also provide valuable enrichment for your dog.</li>
                        <li>This improves their overall happiness and day-to-day enjoyment; some dog breeds (such as Golden Retrievers or German shepherds) especially love having tasks and being able to complete skills for their owners making dog training an essential activity.</li>
                        <li>Additionally, dog training can increase the bond between you and your dog. As you spend time working on skills with your pup and having daily training sessions, you can improve the closeness of you and your animal and create a lifelong bond that provides both of you happiness and a sense of enjoyment with the other’s presence.</li>
                    </ol>
